{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e0a1f3b0-0000-4000-8000-c0a1f3b0e060",
    "name": "log-processor-service (P5.4 cortex.anomalies.v1 publisher)",
    "description": "Postman v2.1 collection for log-processor-service (P5.4 / ADR-0031). Covers every HTTP-reachable surface exposed by log-processor-service after P5.0/P5.0a/P5.1/P5.2/P5.3/P5.4 on :8095: actuator (health/liveness/readiness/info/metrics/prometheus/beans) + end-to-end pipeline assertion that an anomaly published via log-gateway -> log-ingest-service -> Kafka -> log-processor increments cortex.processor.events.consumed_total + cortex.processor.events.classified_total{outcome=anomaly} + cortex.processor.anomalies.published_total (P5.4 / ADR-0031, bootstrap-registered so the family is always present in the scrape; asserted unconditionally) on the processor's /actuator/prometheus scrape; sink counters cortex.processor.sink.{loki,quickwit}.published_total are asserted conditionally on family presence (P5.3 / ADR-0030 -- disabled sinks do not false-fail). Folder order matters: Auth populates jwt, Metrics-Baseline snapshots counters, Pipeline publishes through the gateway, Metrics-After asserts the deltas. Run with --bail. Boot the full stack with scripts/p5-4/boot-full-stack.ps1 first (sets CORTEX_PROCESSOR_CLASSIFIER=spring-ai + SPRING_AI_OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8094 + CORTEX_PROCESSOR_SINKS_{LOKI,QUICKWIT}_ENABLED=true so the WireMock-stubbed Ollama deterministically returns anomaly verdicts AND the AnomaliesPublisher writes to cortex.anomalies.v1).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "if (!pm.variables.get('request_id')) {",
          "    pm.variables.set('request_id', 'pm-' + Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 12));",
          "}",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Request-Id', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Correlation-ID', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "const tenant = pm.environment.get('tenant_id');",
          "if (tenant) { pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Tenant-Id', value: tenant }); }",
          "const token = pm.environment.get('jwt');",
          "if (token && !pm.request.headers.has('Authorization')) {",
          "    pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Authorization', value: 'Bearer ' + token });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "pm.test('response under 5000 ms (actuator + pipeline tolerated)', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(5000);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Login against log-gateway and populate jwt for downstream Pipeline folder. Skipped when {{gateway_base_url}} is empty (e.g. running Newman against a processor-only deployment).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/v1/auth/login -> 200 + populate jwt",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{auth_username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{auth_password}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gateway_base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": [ "{{gateway_base_url}}" ],
              "path": [ "api", "v1", "auth", "login" ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('accessToken populated', function () { pm.expect(body.accessToken).to.be.a('string').that.is.not.empty; });",
                  "pm.test('refreshToken populated', function () { pm.expect(body.refreshToken).to.be.a('string').that.is.not.empty; });",
                  "pm.environment.set('jwt', body.accessToken);",
                  "pm.environment.set('refresh_token', body.refreshToken);",
                  "const headerB64 = body.accessToken.split('.')[0];",
                  "const headerJson = JSON.parse(Buffer.from(headerB64.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'), 'base64').toString('utf8'));",
                  "pm.test('JWT alg=HS256 per ADR-0015', function () { pm.expect(headerJson.alg).to.equal('HS256'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
